  "texts": [
    "where the minimum time step t diff is mainly determined by the ambipolar term (t Ambi = min(x 2, y 2, z 2)/η A)).",
    "The parameter N STS is the number of substeps, and ν is a damping parameter associated with the Chebyshev polynomials.",
    "The values of the pair of the parameters (N STS, ν) control the stability, accuracy, and speed of the method.",
    "By selecting ν close to unity the superstep becomes smaller and the method is more accurate, but the gain from applying the STS scheme decreases.",
    "By selecting ν close to zero the system may become unstable at some point, but the benefit from applying the STS is larger (see González-Morales et al., 2018, for details)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "By selecting ν close to zero the system may become unstable at some point, but the benefit from applying the STS is larger (see González-Morales et al., 2018, for details)."
